           <li>{{ city }}: {{ items|map(attribute="name")|join(", ") }}</li>
         {% endfor %}</ul>
 
+    By default, strings are compared case-insensitively. Set
+    ``case_sensitive`` to ``True`` to compare case-sensitively.
+
+    Set ``with_counts`` to ``True`` to include the number of items in
+    each group. ``groupby`` will then yield ``(grouper, list, count)``
+    tuples instead.
+
+    .. sourcecode:: html+jinja
+
+        <ul>{% for city, items, count in users|groupby("city", with_counts=True) %}
+          <li>{{ city }} ({{ count }})</li>
+        {% endfor %}</ul>
+
+    .. versionchanged:: 3.1
+        Added the ``case_sensitive`` parameter. Added the ``with_counts``
+        parameter.
+
     .. versionchanged:: 3.0
         Added the ``default`` parameter.
 
